    <section name="Usage Overview">
      <p>BRUT provides three test types for brXM delivery tier testing. Choose based on what you're testing:</p>

      <table>
        <tr><th>Testing...</th><th>Use</th><th>Guide</th></tr>
        <tr>
          <td>JAX-RS REST endpoints</td>
          <td><code>@BrxmJaxrsTest</code></td>
          <td><a href="testing/jaxrs-testing.html">JAX-RS Testing</a></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Page Model API responses</td>
          <td><code>@BrxmPageModelTest</code></td>
          <td><a href="testing/pagemodel-testing.html">Page Model Testing</a></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>HST Components</td>
          <td><code>@BrxmComponentTest</code></td>
          <td><a href="testing/component-testing.html">Component Testing</a></td>
        </tr>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section name="Quick Example">
      <div class="brush: java">
        <source><![CDATA[
@BrxmJaxrsTest(resources = {HelloResource.class})
class MyApiTest {

    @Test
    void testEndpoint(DynamicJaxrsTest brxm) {
        String response = brxm.request()
            .get("/site/api/hello/world")
            .execute();

        assertEquals("Hello, World!", response);
    }
}
        ]]></source>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section name="Key Features">
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Parameter Injection</strong> - No IDE warnings, standard JUnit 5 pattern</li>
        <li><strong>Zero-Config</strong> - Auto-detection of bean packages, HST root, Spring configs</li>
        <li><strong>Fluent Request API</strong> - <code>brxm.request().get("/api").execute()</code></li>
        <li><strong>Typed JSON Responses</strong> - <code>executeAs(User.class)</code>, <code>executeWithStatus()</code></li>
        <li><strong>No Inheritance</strong> - Uses JUnit 5 extensions, not abstract base classes</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section name="Importing Nodes">
      <p>You can import nodes using the <a href="apidocs/org/bloomreach/forge/brut/common/repository/utils/ImporterUtils.html">ImporterUtils</a> from the <code>brut-common</code> module.</p>
      <div class="brush: java">
        <source><![CDATA[
import java.net.URL;
import org.bloomreach.forge.brut.common.repository.utils.ImporterUtils;

URL resource = getClass().getResource("/news.yaml");
ImporterUtils.importYaml(resource, rootNode, "/content/documents/mychannel", "hippostd:folder");
        ]]></source>
      </div>
      <p>See <a href="testing/stubbing-data.html">Stubbing Test Data</a> for YAML structure and patterns.</p>
    </section>

